			<div id = "comment-13984" class = "comment">
				<p>Yes, exactly, that is what is meant by _interoceptive_ (sensing from within) versus _exteroceptive_ (sending from outside). To avoid dead reckoning errors from odometry you _need_ exteroceptive sensors -- if you pick up the robot it doesn't know it isn't touching the floor anymore so it just keeps integrating. Systems to give you accurate global positioning are not cheap and always difficult to configure properly, so don't be too discouraged.</p>
			</div>
